The "Societal RBAC" Framework
In your Lighthouse repository, you can define these roles not as "powers," but as "Functional Obligations." Here is how you can structure the "Permissions" for these pillars:

1. The Guardians (Judiciary, Bureaucracy: IAS/IPS)
Role: Auditor-General of Integrity.

Permission: Access to "Real-Time Fiscal Dashboards" and "Policy Impact Data."

Obligation: They do not have the role to create political content, but they have the "Read/Write" access to verify the feasibility of manifestos.

The "Constraint": They are strictly forbidden from participating in "political theater." Their role is to provide the "Ground Truth" on debt, law, and order.

2. The Moral Compass (Religious Institutions, NGOs)
Role: Custodian of Human Welfare.

Permission: "Read Access" to social outcomes. They can "View" the state of the citizenry (poverty, education, safety).

Obligation: To act as the "Alert System." When the government’s actions (or the political theater) cross the line into dehumanizing the population, they have the "Write" permission to issue a "Dharma Audit" (a public call for moral recalibration).

3. The Signal Boosters (Media & AI Engines)
Role: Information Steward.

Permission: Access to "Data Aggregation."

Obligation: They lose the permission to "Amplify Contempt." Under this RBAC model, their primary role is to host the "Pre-Election Fiscal Dashboard." Any media outlet that prioritizes "Vasai Padum" (insult content) over "Fiscal Feasibility" loses its Steward designation, effectively being tagged as "Noise."

4. The Sovereigns (The Citizens)
Role: System Auditor.

Permission: "Full Audit Access." They have the right to view the feasibility studies and the fiscal impact of every promise.

Constraint: They must exercise their role by rejecting "Sticker/Meme" politics and instead referencing the Lighthouse standard.
